results.abstract: State Dept spokesman Hodding Carter 3d assails Dole for publicizing confidential cablegram for purpose of gaining support for proposed treaty revisions, says Dole amendments would wreck treaties; Carter and Acting State Sec Warren Christopher also reiterate Adm's position that under 1 of 2 pacts, so-called neutrality treaty with Panama, US would have right indefinitely to take any steps necessary to defend canal; Dole argues that best way to assure adherence to Adm's interpretations is to attach legally binding amendments and reservations to treaties; concedes action would require renegotiation of some portions with Panama, testimony, Sen Foreign Relations Com hearing; Sens Church and Glenn comment (M)

results.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Oct. 5 The State Department assailed Senator Robert Dole today for having made public a confidential cablegram from the American Embassy in Panama for the purpose of gaining support for the treaty revisions he was proposing.
